<HEADLINE>
ROENICK GETS EARLY PENALTIES
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MATT McHALE  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   Phoenix captain Keith Tkachuk missed Sunday night's game with
back spasms. That made it even more surprising when the Kings were
able to dupe the Coyotes' leading scorer, Jeremy Roenick, into two
five-minute fighting penalties in the first period.
</P>
<P>
   The first came 4:18 into the game when Roenick and fourth-line
winger Dan Bylsma tangled in the Kings' end. The second came with
2:35 left and involved Len Barrie along the left boards.
</P>
<P>
   The Kings will never mind losing Bylsma, a healthy scratch most
of the season, and Barrie, a minor league call-up playing on the
fourth line, if they can get a player of Roenick's status out of
the game.
</P>
<P>
   Barrie, a scorer throughout his minor-league career, played five
weeks on the Kings' first line when Jozef Stumpel was sidelined
with a hernia. Stumpel returned Wednesday and Barrie has been moved
back to the fourth line.
</P>
<P>
   Roenick centers the Coyotes' first line, usually a finesse
position. But he leads the team with 64 penalty minutes. Ian
Laperriere, center on the Kings' third line, or enforcer line,
leads the NHL with 115 penalty minutes. This includes two 10-minute
misconduct penalty and a five-minute major penalty early in the
second period.
</P>
<P>
   But Roenick, who leads the Coyotes with 17 goals and 43 points,
is known for his physical play as well. Earlier this season, he was
suspended five games for slashing Chicago's Tony Amonte.
</P>
<P>
   Berg out: The Kings continued to shuffle their defensive
pairings after Aki Berg was sidelined with a rib injury in
Wednesday's 2-1 loss at San Jose.
</P>
<P>
   Berg's place on the active roster was taken by Jere Karalahti,
who received his first NHL point when he assisted on Laperriere's
first-period goal.
</P>
<P>
   Berg had played two of his better games last week in place of
injured captain Rob Blake (groin). His effectiveness was limited
against San Jose because of the rib injury.
</P>
<P>
   Jaroslav Modry, a frequent healthy scratch this season, was
active in place of Garry Galley, who has missed two games with a
concussion.!dlim!!end!
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
