<P>
   RIGOLETTO-OPERA-REVIEW (New York) _ Real opera fans relish
nothing more than a nice, contentious debate about a singer, and
Paolo Gavanelli is going to provoke one for sure. The Italian
baritone sang the title role in Verdi's ``Rigoletto'' at the
Metropolitan Opera on Friday night, the first performance this
season of the 1989 Otto Schenk production. By Anthony Tommasini.
</P>
<P>
   (ART ADV: Photo [NYT3) has been sent to NYT photo clients.)
</P>
<P>
   SITWELL-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ There have been individual
biographies of Edith and Sacheverell and at least two major studies
of the Sitwells as a group and cultural phenomenon. Up to now there
had been no biography of Sir Osbert Sitwell, and Philip Ziegler,
best known for his life of Lord Mountbatten, has written one:
``Osbert Sitwell'' (Knopf). By Richard Eder.
</P>
