<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-BILLS-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BILLS CONTROL OWN FATE 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ALLEN LESSELS  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   FOXBOROUGH, Mass. _ The Bills took the long way around and had
to stare down a couple of Adam Vinatieri field goals to do it, but
at the end they knocked off the Patriots and remained in control of
their immediate playoff future.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is a big, important win for us to win 10 games,'' said
coach Wade Phillips, whose team improved to 10-5. ``We don't know
where we are in the playoffs yet because of other games, but it was
a giant step toward that.''
</P>
<P>
   The Bills could have sneaked in for sure Sunday night, but
Seattle won, and they could get in Monday night if Miami loses. An
assortment of things can happen next weekend, but if nothing else
the Bills can win and get in.
</P>
<P>
   ``More than anything, in the playoff hunt, this is so
meaningful,'' said quarterback Doug Flutie. ``I mean, if we'd lost
this game, we'd have our backs against the wall and need help next
week and have all that kind of stuff going on. Now, we could
potentially lock up the game this week.''
</P>
<P>
   Bruce Smith isn't interested in the machinations of the whole
thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``Winning takes care of everything,'' the veteran defensive end
said. ``If we win them all, we'll be in the playoffs.''
</P>
<P>
   And yes, he wanted to make it clear, the Bills did slip from
their heyday of four straight Super Bowl appearances in the early
'90s. They missed the playoffs in 1994 and 1997. No, he said, with
all due respect, he has no advice to the Patriots on how to deal
with any slipping fortunes.
</P>
<P>
   ``That's their problem,'' Smith said. ``We've got enough
problems.''
</P>
<P>
   One of them they can take care of next week.
</P>
<P>
   ``We win one more at home and we'll be in (the playoffs) for
sure,'' Phillips said.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, that task is not exactly simple either: The Bills
have the Colts at home Sunday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
