<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    A few good sites
 &HT;    By Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ www.synge.com/insulter.html _ Synge.com's insult
generator is one of the better ones on the Net. Pick something
you'd like to harp on (from bad breath to bad work habits), type in
the intended's e-mail address and the site will generate a
one-liner insult you can send anonymously. You can even choose the
level of rudeness (from a harmless ``one'' to a devastatingly rude
``four''). Use with caution.
</P>
<P>
   sideswipe.com _ The first thing you see when you arrive at
Sideswipe.com is a message reading ``Cats may cease to function
properly after midnight, 31 December 1999.'' And it only gets
stranger. Sixty-six unrelated Web page are strung together. Some
are humorous, others are tasteless, some are just weird. An
interesting way to kill 15 minutes online.
</P>
<P>
   www.tothepoint.fi/flash/index.html _ While the English version
of this Finnish Web site for a company called To The Point is
nothing to write your system administrator about, the
Finnish-language Flash-enabled version is a beautiful demonstration
of what can be done with current Web animation. Each link on the
site flows seamlessly into another cleverly designed section. We
can't understand what it says, but we're impressed nonetheless.
</P>
<P>
   members.tripod.com/(tilde)SJEWELRYS/shopper.html _ Everybody
likes free stuff, and it doesn't get much freer than Daily
Freebies, a site that offers a slew of free catalogs, samples and
special offers. Use the power of the Internet to clog your mailbox
with ill-gotten gains.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
