 &HT;    Wand-ers never cease
 &HT;    By Gregory Kallenberg
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _ Oh boy! The red, strobing Taxi Wand is back! But
this time, it's been outfitted in silver, plays ``Auld Lang Syne''
and comes with a stylin' silver lanyard with ``01012000'' printed
on it. It also changed its name. This incarnation of the Taxi Wand
is remonikered the Millennium Wand 2000 ($8, www.wandworld.com) and
it is sure to help bring in the New Year, the New Century and the
New Millennium with a bang. Just press the button and the red light
flashes and you hear everyone's favorite end-of-the-year song. It's
like having an instant New Year's party in your hand. I guess the
only question left to ask is if it's Y2K compliant.
