<SLUG> BC-TECH-WEBSHOP28-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Shopping on the Web
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _spun.com _ Waterloo Records might still be the
best place to buy, sell and trade CDs, but if you want to do it
online, spun.com is a good place to start. By entering CDs you want
to unload, you can use the online credit to go shopping for other
new and used CDs. Spun will send you your goods and ship you a
returnable box to complete the exchange. The site assures customers
that used CDs are quality-inspected.
</P>
<P>
   MUST BUY: A used copy of Lucinda Williams' ``Car Wheels on a
Gravel Road'' for $7.99 plus shipping.
</P>
<P>
   mercata.com _ If you've seen mercata.com's TV commercials, you
probably remember them well: couples together and in bed obsess
suggestively about an unspecified object that ``keeps going down.''
The Web site the commercials are promoting is based on this simple
concept: group buying power. When you sign up as a power buyer, you
can bid on items such as DVD players and TVs, then watch as the
prices continue to go down as more people sign on. The downside: If
you want to buy something that's not too popular, it can be awfully
lonely without your group buying friends.
</P>
<P>
   MUST BUY: We don't know _ we're still seeing how far the prices
fall on a new DVD player.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
