 &HT;    Win FanFest tickets and a cow
 &HT;    By Theresa Walsh Giarrusso
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ Ten kids will win four passes each to the Peach Bowl
FanFest on Thursday and win a Chick-fil-A cow and ``cowlendar.''
All you have to do is answer three questions about the bowl. Call
404-760-0965 and read your answers and give your name and number.
You will be notified by phone on Tuesday if you've won. You'll find
the answers at www.chick-fil-apeachbowl.com. You must be 6 to 14 to
enter. The first 10 correct callers will be chosen. Here are the
questions: 1. When the Chick-fil-A Peach Bowl tickets sold out,
what was the total number of seats filled at the Georgia Dome? 2.
How many years has Atlanta hosted the Peach Bowl? 3. What are the
mascots of this year's Peach Bowl teams?
</P>
<P>
   IT'S MY MILLENNIUM FIRST
</P>
<P>
   Who will see the first sunrise of the new millennium? Several
island nations in the South Pacific, including Fiji and New
Zealand, are claiming that distinction. The world is divided into
24 time zones. The time changes usually by an hour from zone to
zone. At the International Date Line, which runs through the
Pacific Ocean, the date changes. Dawn on Jan. 1 will arrive on New
Zealand 17 hours before it hits Georgia.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
