</P>
<P>
   The Cassini spacecraft, now bound for Saturn, will drop a probe
through Titan's clouds in 2004 for a firsthand look. Meanwhile, Max
plans to use the Keck telescope to make a crude map of Titan's
composition.
</P>
<P>
   ``With a probe, you get lots and lots of data about just one
place,'' Max says. ``We hope to survey the entire surface.
</P>
