<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FILM-FANTASIA-Y2K-PARTY-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ALL YOU NEED IS $2,000
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
(Eds: With FILM-FANTASIA-FEATURE) 
By VALERIE KUKLENSKI 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Still without plans for New Year's Eve? Looking for something
special that doesn't involve travel? Walt Disney Pictures still has
tickets available for the West Coast premiere of ``Fantasia 2000,''
which will be screened in the eye-popping IMAX format accompanied
live by the 120-piece London Philharmonia orchestra.
</P>
<P>
   The black-tie affair at Pasadena Civic Auditorium for 2,000
revelers opens with a gourmet feast created by Joachim Splichal and
Patina Catering. Next comes the screening, then dancing to '70s pop
stars Chicago and swing band Big Bad Voodoo Daddy. At midnight
there will be champagne, pyrotechnics and confetti.
</P>
<P>
   Of course, ``special'' is the opposite of ``cheap.'' Tickets
cost $2,000 each (think of it as $1 a year), or $20,000 for a table
of 10. A portion of that price goes to California Institute of the
Arts, the training ground for many Disney artists. For reservations
and information _ including how to dodge the Tournament of Roses
traffic snarls _ call (818) 238-1095. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
