 For Release TUESDAY AMs, December 28, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call  &UR; 888-346-9867  &LR; or  &UR; 888-603-1036 &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COSTLY-RESCUES (Undated) _ Search and rescue workers complain
that thrillseekers are plunging into the wilderness unprepared,
lulled into false security by cellphones and global positioning
systems. Then, when something goes wrong, they call for help. Now
comes the backlash: New Hampshire's Fish and Game Department is
getting ready to bill reckless hikers who end up having to be
rescued. By Ellen Barry. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
