HOSPITALS (Phoenix) - Phoenix area hospitals are swamped - with the
flu. Scottsdale Healthcare Osborn set a record Sunday - seeing 182
patients, the majority of which had the flu. Some hospitals advise
people with flu symptoms to come on in, while others advise
patients to see their family doctors first. One reason is patients
feel so horrible with this strain of the flu they think they could
die and wonder, `What if this isn't the flu?` says one hospital
spokeswoman. We check in with different hospitals and check to see
if this is affecting people who arrive at ERs with real
emergencies. By HEALTH ROMERO. Story will move in the ``A''
