</P>
<P>
   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   GORE-CAMPAIGN (Washington) _ It is hard now to think of a
candidate who has undergone more transformations in a shorter
period than Al Gore. Now Gore faces the most critical weeks of his
political career, a hectic two-and-a-half-month campaign sprint
through Iowa, New Hampshire, New York, California and the Deep
South that will most likely determine whether his frantic
self-makeover and the doubts he has tried to raise about Bill
Bradley have worked, or whether he will be denied what he once
viewed as his rightful ``promotion.'' A state of the campaign
feature by Katharine Q. Seelye. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in
``p'' news file.) 1,900 words.
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON-PHARMACY (Washington) _ Details of new administration
initiative on pharmaceuticals. By Robert Pear. (Scheduled to move
by 9 p.m. ET in ``w'' news file.) 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAVIA-SOLDIER (Leskovac, Yugoslavia) _ For Vlada, a unit
commander for the Yugoslav army during the Kosovo war, the months
since have been a wretched period of guilt, poverty, doubt and
repression, stemming from his participation in anti-government
demonstrations in this conservative, wary town. He thinks he's
slightly mad; he thinks everyone else in Leskovac is, too. By
Steven Erlanger. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,800
words.
</P>
<P>
   BOTTOM
</P>
<P>
   3-column photo reefer to EUROPE-STORM; story inside.
</P>
<P>
   CHINA-QIGONG (Beijing) _ A thriving anti-cancer movement based
on breathing exercises and strenuous walking is one of hundreds of
qigong variants operating in China, even as the authorities crack
down on one prominent offshoot, Falun Gong, and step up scrutiny of
the others. The official acceptance of some qigong sects while
others are crushed is part of a long, often tortuous effort by the
government to distinguish supposedly scientific, beneficial qigong
from practices labeled superstitious and then curbed. By Erik
Eckholm. (The story has moved in ``i'' news file.) 1,500 words.
</P>
<P>
   With photo NYT18.
</P>
