<P>
   RUSSIA-OIL (Moscow) _ On its face, it is no great shakes that
Russia's sixth-biggest oil company, Sibneft, unveiled a spiffy new
green-and-blue logo in April. What makes it a symbolic symbol
indeed is the logo's two flavors: traditional Cyrillic, for
Russians, and English, for almost everyone else. For an industry
that has exemplified this nation's hand-on-the-throat style of
business, there may be no better metaphor. By Michael Wines.
</P>
