<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MILLENNIUM-ALCOHOLICS (Washington) _ As partygoers plan to
christen the next millennium with the New Year's Eve bash of the
century, pressure is greater than ever to drink. As a result,
recovering alcoholics are searching for ways to celebrate without
liquor. By JUDY HOLLAND. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL NEWS (``a'' category)
</P>
<P>
   SHUTTLE-HUBBLE (Cape Canaveral, Fla.) _ The space shuttle
Discovery returns to Earth after an eight-day trip to repair the
Hubble Space Telescope. By MARK CARREAU.
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS/FINANCIAL NEWS (``f'' category)
</P>
<P>
   Y2K-WORKING (Houston) _ It is bad enough to forfeit a New Year's
Eve for your job, but it is really tough to have to clock in on
what has been billed as the party night of the century.
Consequently, many companies are doing what they can to make the
situation more palatable for the employees who have to work Friday
night. By L.M. SIXEL. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-COWBOYS (Dallas) _ The Dallas Cowboys once again find
themselves in a position to make it to the playoffs despite a 7-8
record. The Cowboys play the New York Giants in the regular-season
finale for both teams. By JODY GOLDSTEIN.
</P>
<P>
   FBC-ALAMO (San Antonio) _ Texas A&AMP;M has been on an emotional
roller-coaster. Penn State has lost its last three after being a
consensus favorite to play for the national championship. The teams
clash Tuesday night in the Alamo Bowl in San Antonio. By NEIL
HOHLFELD.
</P>
<P>
   With: FBC-LOPEZ-COLUMN
</P>
<P>
   FBC-COTTON-ARKANSAS (Dallas) _ Arkansas has won games it
expected to lose and lost games it expected to win in this
up-and-down season. By TERRY BLOUNT.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-ROCKETS (Houston) _ The staggering Houston Rockets return
home to face the Toronto Raptors in National Basketball Association
action. JONATHAN FEIGEN.
</P>
<P>
   BKN-RAPTORS (Houston) _ Vince Carter and the explosive Toronto
Raptors are making names for themselves in the National Basketball
Association. The road show comes to the Compaq Center on Tuesday
night. By MICHAEL MURPHY.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (''k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Barbara Bush is leading a Bush
family effort to modify or eliminate the Republican platform plank
that calls for criminalizing all abortion, even one to save the
life of the mother. Bob Dole couldn't get rid of it in 1996, but
never underestimate Bar, let alone her son George W., the GOP
presidential front-runner. By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already filed.)
</P>
