<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-CORRECTIONS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR TUESDAY, DEC. 28
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Tuesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-SAFRICA-SUBURBS-NYT (moved on Thursday, Dec. 23)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, Dec. 23,
about new houses for blacks built by the South African government
misstated the cost of the houses. It was $2 billion, not $6
billion.
</P>
<P>
   BC-INDIA-HIJACK-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 24,
about the seizure of an Indian Airlines jetliner misstated the
ethnicity of the hijackers and omitted attribution for the
description. It was the BBC that described them as Sikhs, as noted
elsewhere in the article. But the hijackers are now believed to be
Islamic militants who support Kashmir's independence from India.
</P>
<P>
   BC-HOLIDAY-WORKERS-NYT (moved on Friday, Dec. 24)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Friday, Dec. 24,
about companies' staffing plans for New Year's Eve misstated the
time difference between New York and New Zealand in describing
plans to monitor early signs of trouble around the world. New
Zealand is 18 hours ahead of New York, not 16.
</P>
<P>
   BC-BEEF-RECALL-NYT (moved on Saturday, Dec. 25)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Saturday, Dec. 25,
about a recall of meat by Supreme Beef Processors Inc. of Dallas
referred imprecisely to the ``sell by'' date marked on the affected
packages. It was Dec. 28, not Dec. 28 or earlier.
</P>
<P>
   BC-ONLINE-NEWS-NYT (moved on Sunday, Dec. 26)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, Dec. 26,
about Internet sites run by major news organizations referred
imprecisely to the operations of the staff that provides financial
news updates to The New York Times on the Web and TheStreet.com.
The staff is a joint venture of The New York Times and
TheStreet.com _ not operated solely by TheStreet.com, in which The
Times also has a financial interest.
</P>
<P>
   BC-CIR-COMPUTER-COLUMN-NYT (moved on Wednesday, Dec. 22)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Wednesday, Dec.
22, about checking the Y2K compliance of personal computers,
misstated the Web address of a Y2K reference page at the ZDNet
site. It is www.zdnet.com/zdhelp/filters/y2k.
</P>
</TEXT>
