<HEADLINE>
KANSAS CITY BOARD OF TRADE ENHANCES SOME TRADING CONTRACTS 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By VICTORIA SIZEMORE LONG  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ The Kansas City Board of Trade has taken
several steps to enhance some of its trading contracts.
</P>
<P>
   On the exchange's Isdex Internet stock-index contract, the
exchange has added the companies Scient and Intraware and removed
CDNow and Axent Technologies}.
</P>
<P>
   Isdex, the Internet Stock Index created by internet.com Corp.,
contains 50 stocks of publicly traded U.S. companies that derive
revenue primarily from the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   The Isdex is reviewed on a regular basis to add or delete stocks
that best represent Internet diversity for investors.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the exchange has approved plans to simplify its
offerings on its Value Line stock index.
</P>
<P>
   Pending approval by the Commodity Futures Trading Commission,
the Kansas City Board of Trade will eliminate its Value Line stock
index futures contract with a value of $250 times the futures
price. The exchange also will drop the word ``Mini'' from its Mini
Value Line futures and options contract with a value of $100 times
the futures price.
</P>
<P>
   This will leave the exchange trading one futures and options
contract called the Value Line, with the same $100 multiplier that
has previously been referred to as the ``Mini.''
</P>
<P>
   ``This change will simplify the exchange's offering in the Value
Line, while maintaining the product that customers have gravitated
toward,'' said Michael Braude, president of the exchange.
``Smaller-sized stock index contracts truly are the wave of the
future.''
</P>
<P>
   The changes are expected to take effect March 20, the first
business day following the March 2000 futures contract expiration.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
