A0356 &Cx1f; taf-z
u a BC-EXP-NY-NIGHTCLUB-SHOO     12-27 0449
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EXP-NY-NIGHTCLUB-SHOOTING-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
3 HURT IN CLUB SHOOTINGS; PUFFY COMBS FACES GUN POSSESSION
CHARGES 
</HEADLINE>
  (EDS: This article is part of TIMES EXPRESS. It is a condensed
version of a story that will appear in tomorrow's New York Times.) 
(jw) 
 By WILLIAM K. RASHBAUM   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Sean (Puffy) Combs, the multimillionaire rap
entrepreneur, whose career and East Hampton parties have been
fodder for the gossip columns, was arrested on gun possession
charges with actress and singer Jennifer Lopez after shots were
fired at a Midtown dance club early Monday, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Three people were wounded by gunfire at 2:55 a.m. at Club NY,
half a block west of Times Square, police said. Police described
the victims as bystanders and said that none suffered
life-threatening injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Neither Ms. Lopez nor Combs was charged in connection with the
shootings; Ms. Lopez was later released.
</P>
<P>
   A rap performer, Jamal Barrows, 19, who was in Combs' group, was
charged with three counts of attempted murder and criminal
possession of a weapon, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Prosecutors also said that Combs drew a gun in the fracas, but,
through a spokesman, Combs denied that he was involved. An
arraignment was scheduled for late Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Police Commissioner Howard Safir said Combs, 30, and Ms. Lopez,
29, who both fled after the shooting, were arrested along with
Combs' bodyguard and his driver on gun possession charges, because
a stolen pistol was found in the vehicle. The Manhattan District
Attorney's office later decided to release Ms. Lopez, saying they
had evaluated the evidence and had declined to prosecute. The gun
found in the vehicle was not the same one used in the shootings in
the club, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said Ms. Lopez, who has been romantically linked to
Combs, was released because she was unaware that the gun was in the
car and because she cooperated with the police.
</P>
<P>
   Also arrested were Combs' bodyguard, Anthony Jones, 34, and
Combs' driver, Wardel Fenderson, 41. Police charged Combs, Jones
and Fenderson with criminal possession of a weapon and criminal
possession of stolen property, because the 9-millimeter Smith &AMP;
Wesson Model 915 pistol found in the Navigator was reported stolen
in Georgia, authorities said. Jones was also charged with marijuana
possession, police said.
</P>
<P>
   Eric Funk, the club's general manager, said Combs and Ms. Lopez
arrived with an entourage of about 30 after midnight and spent most
of the time in a VIP section set off from the rest of the club by
velvet ropes.
</P>
<P>
   Funk said club patrons were searched and screened with a metal
detector, but he could not say how the guns got inside.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
